  <s:part>
    <s:part-title>Usage</s:part-title>
    <s:part-contents/>
    <s:section>
      <s:section-title>Usage</s:section-title>
      <s:paragraph>
        The package uses the <s:term s:type="type">char</s:term> type to store
        values of the <s:term s:type="type">binary16</s:term> type. To convert
        a double-precision value <s:term s:type="constant">32.0</s:term> to
        <s:term s:type="type">binary16</s:term> format:
      </s:paragraph>
      <s:formal-item s:kind="examples">
        <s:formal-item-title>Packing</s:formal-item-title>
        <s:verbatim><![CDATA[
final char k = Binary16.packDouble(32.0);
]]></s:verbatim>
      </s:formal-item>
      <s:paragraph>
        To unpack values from the <s:term s:type="type">binary16</s:term> format:
      </s:paragraph>
      <s:formal-item s:kind="examples">
        <s:formal-item-title>Packing</s:formal-item-title>
        <s:verbatim><![CDATA[
final double r = Binary16.unpackDouble(k);
]]></s:verbatim>
      </s:formal-item>
      <s:paragraph>
        Equivalent functions exist for the single precision 
        <s:term s:type="type">float</s:term> type. Consult the
        <s:link-external s:target="apidocs">Javadoc</s:link-external> for
        the full list.
      </s:paragraph>
    </s:section>
  </s:part>

